        <name>GetAttributeIndices</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Returns a vector of size N indices. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Initially this contains indices [0 ... N-1], however when the <ref refid="class_particles_1a5ce4f1078bbd15c80dc12338a8b874a8" kindref="member">Sort()</ref> method is called, the particle positions in the arrays will change. The Indices array will also change so you can still refer to the same particle via its attribute index. Example: if a particle is in <ref refid="class_particles_1af86654babc9a26b508954328f4a08994" kindref="member">GetPhysicalAttributes()</ref>[3], then <ref refid="class_particles_1a612184eb90bd12a7f08053436e334b07" kindref="member">GetAttributeIndices()</ref>[3] will return its original index before any sorting took place. </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/nfs/2017/t/twalton/bomberman/github/src/Particles.hpp" line="72" column="1" bodyfile="/nfs/2017/t/twalton/bomberman/github/src/Particles.cpp" bodystart="83" bodyend="86"/>
      </memberdef>
